[1
Ebola Haemorrhagic Fever In Uganda - WHO Update 14
--------------------------------------------------
As of Mon 30 Oct 2000, the Ugandan Ministry of Health has reported
cumulative figures of 224 cases, including 73 deaths. [This represents an
increase of 13 cases with one death since the last update. - Mod.CP
In addition to all the participants mentioned in a previous report
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/n2000/october/27october2000.html>,
the Government of Japan is supporting the containment of the outbreak in
Uganda by making available 2 clinicians from the National Institute of
Infectious Diseases and from Sendai Quarantine Station who have arrived in
Gulu to work with the case management team.
******
[2
Date: Mon, 30 Oct 2000 13:43:33 -0500
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: AP Online, filed Mon 30 Oct 2000 06:06 AM EST [edited

Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever Outbreak confined to Gulu Region
--------------------------------------------------------
KAMPALA: As of Mon 30 Oct 2000, the death toll from the outbreak of Ebola
hemorrhagic fever in northern Uganda has risen to 73 after 2 more people
died in the past 48 hours. Francis Omaswa, Director General Of Uganda's
Medical Services, said 19 new cases had also been identified in the last 2
days, bringing the number of known cases to 224. All the confirmed Ebola
cases are in and around the town of Gulu, 223 miles north of Kampala. The
outbreak was confirmed on 14 Oct 2000.
"We continue to receive reports of suspected cases from other parts of the
country. These are being investigated promptly; [so far none of them are
[confirmed cases of Ebola hemorrhagic fever," Omaswa said in a statement.
He also indicated that 21 people had been discharged from hospitals during
the last 48 hours bringing the number who had recovered from the virus to 96.
*******
[3
Date: Tue, 31 Oct 2000 14:55:40 +0100
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: WHO Disease Outbreaks Report, Tue 31 Oct 2000 [edited
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/>

Ebola Haemorrhagic Fever In Uganda - WHO Update 15
--------------------------------------------------
As of Tue 31 October 2000, the Ugandan Ministry of Health has reported
cumulative figures of 239 cases, including 75 deaths. [This represents an
increase of 15 cases with 2 additional deaths during the last 24 hours. -
Mod.CP
A logistician from the International Rescue Committee will be joining the
task force in Gulu district. He will be assisting the Ugandan District
Medical Office with the management of supplies and general transport, as
well as with the deployment of people and teams in the task force.
